        protected java.util.Collection<Tuple> retrieveOpposites(DualInputNode.Side side,
                                                        Tuple signature)
        Helper: retrieves all stored substitutions from the opposite side memory. The results are copied into a new collection; this step has a performance penalty, but avoids ConcurrentModificaton Exceptions when loops are present.
        Returns:
        the collection of opposite substitutions if any, or null if none
